column1: NGR is the Whitworth Institute. Altitudes match.

The inspector notes that some of the 1920s readings are copied from Darley Hall, which is 350m NNE with a different observer. Comparing the readings all of 1923 to 1925 and most of 1922 are either duplicated or within 0.02 inches and have been removed. There are 3 duplicated readings in the period 1920 to 1921. There is only one duplicated reading prior to the 1920s, which is coincidental.
